Eleven people were left injured this morning, 8 May, when a taxi crashed into a tree in Boshoff Rd, Pietermaritzburg.&nbsp;According to spokesperson Russel Meiring, ER24 paramedics arrived at the scene to find that the occupants had already climbed out of the vehicle and that three sustained serious injuries while eight others moderate to minor ones. The driver later told paramedics that he had apparently lost control of the vehicle, causing it to slam into a tree, said Meiring.&nbsp;